 And in that day God shall shine gloriously in counsel on the earth, to exalt and glorify the remnant of Israel. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 3.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And it shall be, that the remnant left in Sion, and the remnant left in Jerusalem, even all that are appointed to life in Jerusalem, shall be called holy. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 4.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 For the Lord shall wash away the filth of the sons and daughters of Sion, and shall purge out the blood from the midst of them, with the spirit of judgment, and the spirit of burning. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 5.}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And he shall come, and it shall be with regard to every place of mount Sion, yea, all the region round about it shall a cloud overshadow by day, and there shall be as
 it were the smoke and light of fire burning by night: and upon all the glory shall be a defense. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 6.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And it shall be for a shadow from the heat, and as a shelter and a hiding place from inclemency of weather and from rain. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 1.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  Now I will sing to my beloved 
a song of my beloved concerning my vineyard. My beloved had a vineyard on a high hill in a fertile place. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 2.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And I made a hedge round it, and dug a trench, and planted a choice vine, and built a tower in the midst of it and dug a place for the wine vat in it: and I waited for it to bring forth grapes, and it brought forth thorns. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 3.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And now, ye dwellers in Jerusalem, and every man of Juda, judge between me and my vineyard. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 4.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 What shall I do any more to my vineyard, that I have not done to it? Whereas I expected it to bring forth grapes, but it has brought forth thorns. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 5.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And now I will tell you what I will do to my vineyard: I will take away its hedge, and it shall be for a spoil; and I will pull down its walls, and it shall be left to be trodden down. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 6.}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And I will forsake my vineyard; and it shall not be pruned, nor dug, and thorns shall come up upon it as on barren land; and I will command the clouds to rain no rain upon it. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 7.}
{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  For the vineyard of the Lord of hosts is the house of Israel, and the men of Juda his beloved plant: I expected it to bring forth judgment, and it brought forth iniquity; and not righteousness, but a cry. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 
