And it came to pass in the year in which king Ozias died, [that] I saw the Lord sitting on a high and exalted throne, and the house was full of his glory. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 2.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And seraphs stood round about him: each one had six wings: and with two they covered [their] face, and with two they covered [their] feet, and with two they flew. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 3.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And one cried to the other, and they said, Holy, holy, holy [is the] Lord of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 4.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And the lintel shook at the voice they uttered, and the house was filled with smoke. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 5.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And I said, Woe is me, for I am pricked to the heart; for being a man, and having unclean lips, and I have seen with mine eyes the King, the Lord of hosts. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 6.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And there was sent to me one of the seraphs, and he had in his hand, a coal, which he had taken off the altar with the tongs: }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 7.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 and he touched my mouth, and said, Behold, this has touched thy lips, and will take away thine iniquities, and will purge off thy sins. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 8.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And I heard the voice of the Lord, saying, Whom shall I send, and who will go to this people? And I said, behold, I am [here], send me. And he said, Go, and say to this people. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 9.}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  Ye shall hear indeed, but ye shall not understand; and ye shall see indeed, but ye shall not perceive. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 10.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 For the heart of this people has become gross, and their ears are dull of hearing, and their eyes have they closed; lest they should see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and un
derstand with their heart, and be converted, and I should heal them. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 11.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And I said, How long O Lord? And he said, Until cities be deserted by reason of their not being inhabited, and the houses by reason of there being no men, and the land shall be left desolate. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 12.}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And after this God shall remove the men far off, and they that are left upon the land shall be multiplied. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 
