 My son, do what I command thee, and deliver thyself; for on thy friend's account thou art come into the power of evil men: faint not, but stir up even thy friend for whom thou art become surety. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 4.}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber with thine eyelids; }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 5.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 that thou mayest deliver thyself as a doe out of the toils, and as a bird out of a snare. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 6.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  Go to the ant, O sluggard; and see, and emulate his ways, and become wiser than he. 
}{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 7.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  For whereas he has no husbandry, nor any one to compel him, and is under no master, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 8.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 he prepares food for himself in the summer, and lays by abundant store in harvest. Or go to the bee, and learn how diligent she is, and how earnestly she is engaged in her work; whose labors kings and private men use for health, and she 
is desired and respected by all: though weak in body, she is advanced by honoring wisdom. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 9.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  How long wilt thou lie, O sluggard? and when wilt thou awake out of sleep? }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 10.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  Thou sleepest a little, and thou restest a little, and thou slumberest a short time, and thou foldest thine arms over thy breast a little. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 11.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 Then poverty comes upon thee as an evil traveler, and want as a swift courier: but if thou be diligent, thine harvest shall arrive as a fountain, and poverty shall flee away as a bad courier. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 12.}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  A foolish man and a transgressor goes in ways that are not good. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 13.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And the same winks with the eye, and makes a sign with his foot, and teaches with the beckonings of his fingers. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 14.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 His perverse heart devises evils: at all times such a one causes troubles to a city. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 15.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  Therefore his destruction shall come suddenly; overthrow and irretrievable ruin. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 16.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  For he rejoices in all things which God hates, and he is ruined by reason of impurity of soul. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 17.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 The eye of the haughty, a tongue unjust, hands shedding the blood of the just; }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 18.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  and a heart devising evil thoughts, and feet hastening to do evil, -- are hateful to God. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 19.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  An unjust witness kindles falsehoods, and brings on quarrels between brethren. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 20.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 My son, keep the laws of thy father, and reject not the ordinances of thy mother: }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 
\par }\pard \s21\qj \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 
