And it came to pass in the days of Achaz [the son] of Joatham, the son of Ozias, king of Juda, there came in Rasin king of Aram, and Phakee son of Romelias, king of Israel, against Jerusalem to war against it, but they could not take it. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 2.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And a message was brought to the house of David, saying, Aram has conspired with Ephraim. And his soul was amazed, and the soul of his people, as in a wood 
a tree is moved by the wind. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 3.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And the Lord said to Esaias, Go forth to meet Achaz, thou, and thy son Jasub who is left, to the pool of the upper way of the fuller's field. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 4.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And thou shalt say to him, Take care to be quiet, and fear not, neither let thy
 soul be disheartened because of these two smoking firebrands: for when my fierce anger is over, I will heal again. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 5.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 And [as for] the son of Aram, and the son of Romelias, forasmuch as they have devised an evil counsel [saying], }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 6.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  We will go up against 
Judea, and having conferred with them we will make the son of Tabeel king of it; }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 7.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  thus saith the Lord of hosts, This counsel shall not abide, nor come to pass. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 8.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  But the head of Aram is Damascus, and the head of Damascus, Rasim; and yet within sixty and five years the kingdom of Ephraim shall cease from [being] a people. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 9.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And the head of Ephraim is Somoron, and the head of Somoron the son of Romelias: but if ye believe not, neither will ye at all understand. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 10.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And the Lord again spoke to Achaz, saying, }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 11.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789 
 Ask for thyself a sign of the Lord thy God, in the depth or in the height. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 12.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And Achaz said, I will not ask, neither will I tempt the Lord. }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 13.}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  And he said, Hear ye now, O house of David; is it a little thing for you to contend against the Lord? }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 14.}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid12399789  Therefore the Lord himself shall give you a sign; behold, a virgin shall conceive in the womb, and shall bring forth a son, and thou shalt call his name Emmanuel. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid12399789\charrsid12399789 
