}{\f1\fs16\insrsid14566844\charrsid4868240 9}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid14566844\charrsid14566844  Whether is it easier to say to the sick of the palsy, Thy sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Arise, and take up thy bed, and walk? }{
\f1\fs16\insrsid14566844\charrsid4868240 10}{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid14566844\charrsid14566844  But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins, (he saith to the sick of the palsy) }{\f1\fs16\insrsid14566844\charrsid4868240 11}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid14566844\charrsid14566844  I say unto thee, Arise, and take up thy bed, and}{\fs24\cf1\insrsid14566844  }{\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid14566844\charrsid14566844 go thy way into thine house. }{\f1\fs16\insrsid14566844\charrsid4868240 12}{
\cs31\f35\fs32\insrsid14566844\charrsid14566844  And immediately he arose, took up the bed, and went forth before them all; insomuch that they were all amazed, and glorified God, saying, We never saw it on this fashion.}{\fs24\cf1\insrsid14566844 
